# ArmorIQ x OpenClaw AI Lawyer — Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your keys
# WITHOUT these keys, system runs in simulation mode (same demo, local policy enforcement only)

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ArmorIQ SDK — get your key from platform.armoriq.ai/dashboard/api-keys
# Keys must start with ak_live_ (production) or ak_test_ (testing)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ARMORIQ_API_KEY=ak_live_xxxxxxxxxxxx

# ArmorIQ identity (identifies this agent in the IAP audit trail)
# ARMORIQ_USER_ID=ai-lawyer-user
# ARMORIQ_AGENT_ID=ai-lawyer-agent

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# LLM Keys — optional (system works in simulation mode without these)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# GEMINI_API_KEY=AIzaSy-xxxxxxxxxxxx

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# How the ArmorIQ SDK integration works (read-only info):
#
# 1. LLMBrain generates the action plan (Gemini / Ollama / simulation)
# 2. llm_brain._register_plan_with_armoriq() calls:
#      client.capture_plan()    → registers plan structure with ArmorIQ backend
#      client.get_intent_token() → gets a CSRG Merkle-signed Ed25519 token
# 3. The IntentToken is attached to every IntentObject in the plan
# 4. policy_engine._verify_with_armoriq_sdk() validates the token
# 5. executor._invoke_via_armoriq() calls client.invoke() through the
#      ArmorIQ proxy, which checks Merkle proof for each action
#      → Any action NOT in the original signed plan gets a 409 (intent drift)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
